headline: Micron Stock Is Up 140% and Analysts Predict Even More Big Gains. AI Is Why.
summary: Shares of  Micron Technology  have surged 140% this year, but some analysts see no end in sight to the gains.  Citi Research analyst Christopher Danely argued that dynamic random-access memory, or DRAM, which the kind of storage used in most laptops and personal computers, “will be the next chip to get long-term contracts with the AI food chain given its importance and undersupply.”  Micron gained 6.3% to $204.08, putting the stock on pace for a record high, according to Dow Jones Market Data.

headline: Mortgage rates inch lower, Nvidia & Broadcom boosted by TSM
summary: Yahoo Finance anchor Julie Hyman tracks Thursday's top moving stocks and biggest market stories in this Market Minute. Mortgage rates are slightly lower this week, with the 30-year fixed rate down to 6.27% from 6.3%, according to data from Freddie Mac (FMCC). Chip stocks, including Nvidia (NVDA), Broadcom (AVGO), and Arm Holdings (ARM), are jumping after Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company (TSM) delivered on third quarter earnings results. American Battery Technology Company (ABAT) stock is sinking after the company announced that the US Department of Energy (DOE) canceled its grant funding. Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.

headline: TSMC ADR Premium Tops Two-Decade High as Global Buyers Pile In
summary: Its American depositary receipts are trading at the highest premium to its Taipei shares since 2002, on a 50-day moving average basis.  The ADRs have surged 54% this year, outpacing the 38% gain in the Taiwan listing, as global traders boost bullish bets.  “We are positive on TSMC’s outlook and expect it to raise its full-year 2025 sales growth outlook,” said Rex Chen, a Taipei-based fund manager at Capital Investment Trust Corp.
